            </article>
            <section class="question-long-text" data-uuid="228b6ba0a7534599bc152d0241ac63d1">
                <object type="text/html" data="../../assets/widgets/long_text_question/index.html" class="widget" data-uuid="80fcea30eae74d36b425230e459d640f">
                    <param name="configFile" value="../../widget_data/config/80fcea30eae74d36b425230e459d640f.json" />
                </object>
            </section>
        </section>
        <p data-uuid="07646d47a22d49b799b0f04080f8011e">During that terrible winter at Valley Forge, some 2,000 soldiers died of disease and malnutrition. Amazingly, those who survived not only stayed—they drilled and marched to the orders of Baron von Steuben and became better soldiers.</p>
        <p data-uuid="8dfd4a421131419b89669ed077dca717"> While the soldiers suffered through the winter at Valley Forge, the British lived a life of luxury in Philadelphia. Most of the Patriots had fled the city, leaving only Loyalists and British soldiers. Together they enjoyed the city’s houses, taverns, and theaters, and held parties and balls.<br />
        </p>
